---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | FindVolleyball" description="Why FindVolleyball exists, and what it's trying to fix.">
  <main class="about-page">
    <h1>About Find Volleyball</h1>

    <p>
      Finding a local volleyball game is harder than it should be. Listings are scattered across Reclub, Meetup,
      Goodrec, Facebook groups, and word of mouth — there is no single place to find where you can play.
    </p>

    <p>
      FindVolleyball is a free, community-driven map that tries to fix that: one place to find indoor, grass, and
      beach meetups, with the details that actually matter — cost, skill level, sign-up requirements, schedule —
      filterable in one view instead of buried across five different apps.
    </p>

    <h2>Where we are right now</h2>
    <p>
      We are just getting started. Listings are concentrated in the Greater Los Angeles area for now, seeded from
      first-hand organizer knowledge rather than a large open database — which means coverage is intentionally
      narrow at launch, not comprehensive. New listings go through a quick manual review before they show up on
      the map, to keep the data trustworthy while the community using it is still small.
    </p>

    <h2>Keeping it accurate</h2>
    <p>
      Every listing has a simple "still happening?" vote and a quiet report option, so stale or incorrect listings
      surface naturally instead of sitting on the map indefinitely. If something looks wrong, use either one — it
      helps everyone who looks at the map after you.
    </p>

    <p>
      Want to add a meetup you organize or know about? Use the <a href="/submit">Add Listing</a> button — it takes
      a couple minutes and goes into a short review queue before it's public.
    </p>

    <h2>Feedback</h2>
    <p>
      This is a small, independently-run project, and feedback genuinely shapes what gets built next. Reach out
      anytime at <a href="mailto:robert.tyler.miller@gmail.com">robert.tyler.miller@gmail.com</a>.
    </p>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 32rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 1rem 4rem;

    h1 {
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    h2 {
      margin-top: 2rem;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
    }

    p {
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #333;
    }

    a {
      color: var(--color-accent);
      font-weight: 600;
    }
  }
</style>
